               <head>Kulliyyat of Jami</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kullīyāt-i Jāmī by Jāmī, 1414-1492</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4428-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Very fine calligraphic and illuminated deluxe collection of Jami's poetic works, comprising qaṣāʾid, mas̲navīyāt, ghazaliyāt, tarjīʿāt, tarkībāt, muqaṭṭaʿāt, and rubāʿīyāt </p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning and end; severely damaged by wormholes and staining </p>
                        <p>The opening section consisting of the qaṣāʾid and mas̲navīyāt ends with a dated colophon: in the month of Z̲ī qaʿdah 946/19 March-17 April 1540. Illuminations beginning the ghazaliyāt section remain intact and in good condition </p>
                        <p>Not foliated; estimated 350 folios approximately </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1690">Kullīyāt-i Jāmī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_1690">کليات جامی</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997">Jāmī, 1414-1492</persName>
                        <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176979.0x000001 viaf_90042997" xml:lang="per">جامى</persName>
                     </author>
